HEADWORD: Steamboating
<hw>Steam"boat`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The occupation
or business of running a steamboat, or of transporting merchandise,
passengers, etc., by steamboats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bookbinding)</fld> <def>The shearing of a pile of
books which are as yet uncovered, or out of boards.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steam engine</ent>⟦br⟧
